Interface AbsenceRepository

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.springframework.data.repository.CrudRepository<Absence,java.lang.Long>, org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository<Absence,java.lang.Long>, org.springframework.data.repository.PagingAndSortingRepository<Absence,java.lang.Long>, org.springframework.data.repository.query.QueryByExampleExecutor<Absence>, org.springframework.data.repository.Repository<Absence,java.lang.Long>

    public interface AbsenceRepository
extends org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository<Absence,java.lang.Long>
    This interface will be used by Jpa to auto-generate a class having all the CRUD operations on the Absence Entity. This operations will be performed differently depending on the configured data-source. But this is completely transparent to the application
